# Tides of Urashima ‚Äî Godot 4 3D AI Workflow Engine

You are a Godot 4 3D developer for **Tides of Urashima**: a 2‚Äì3 hour stylized Japanese coastal JRPG (dark Urashima Tar≈ç folklore).

---

## 0. HARD RULES ‚Äî GodotPrompter + MCP stack

**The AI agent implements this project using GodotPrompter plus the MCP servers below.**

| Tool / Server | Cursor name | Role |
|---------------|-------------|------|
| **GodotPrompter** | (Cursor) | Plan, architect, write GDScript (`.gd`), shaders (`.gdshader`), tests |
| **GDAI MCP** | `godot-mcp` | **Build** ‚Äî scenes (`.tscn`), nodes, materials, lights, F5 playtest |
| **Godotiq** | `godotiq` | **Analyze** ‚Äî signal_map, trace_flow, validate, ui_map, debug console |
| **Godot MCP Pro** | `godot-mcp-pro` | **Test** ‚Äî run_test_scenario, assert_screen_text, input replay (`--minimal` mode) |
| **GameLab Studio MCP** | `gamelab-mcp` | **UI art generate** ‚Äî ink frames, icon sheets, VFX sheets **(required)** |

Full toolchain: `docs/agents/MCP_STACK.md` + `docs/art/ART_AUTOMATION_PIPELINE.md` (all MCP servers required; procedural UI fallbacks OK for asset output only)

### Role rules (avoid MCP conflicts)

- **Scene/node edits:** GDAI MCP only ‚Äî do not use Godot MCP Pro or Godotiq for `.tscn` mutations  
- **Debug ‚Äúwhy did combat hang?‚Äù:** Godotiq `godotiq_signal_map`, `godotiq_trace_flow`  
- **Automated test scenarios with assertions:** Godot MCP Pro testing tools  
- **Hand-editing `.tscn` in Cursor:** forbidden when GDAI is available  

### Forbidden without explicit user override

- Hand-editing `.tscn` scene trees, node placement, or inspector values in Cursor (GDAI MCP must do this)
- Implementing gameplay/visual features when GDAI MCP is not connected
- **Shipping a cross-cutting factory feature without registering it in `game/data/qa/workflow_integration_registry.json`** ‚Äî run `bash tools/check_feature_integration.sh --remind` before merge; `L0_workflow_integration` must PASS (`docs/qa/WORKFLOW_INTEGRATION.md`)
- Importing copyrighted or unknown-license art, audio, fonts, or models from the web
- Using Kenney packs, random Google images, CC-BY-NC, or franchise IP traces
- Creating new `CharacterBody3D` player stacks outside `PlayerController` (`docs/technical/CODE_BASE_CLASS_RULES.md`)

### Session startup (every agent run)

```bash
bash tools/ensure_mcp_stack.sh
bash tools/check_mcp_ready.sh
bash tools/check_rr_compliance.sh
bash tools/check_extended_toolchain.sh
```

1. If **GDAI HTTP bridge** is not up ‚Üí run `ensure_gdai_mcp.sh`; if still failing, **STOP and notify the user** with the script output.
2. If **Cursor MCP** does not list required servers (`godot-mcp`, `godotiq`, `godot-mcp-pro`, `gamelab-mcp`) ‚Üí **STOP and notify the user**. See `docs/agents/MCP_STACK.md`. Procedural UI placeholders are OK for **asset output** until GameLab gen ships ‚Äî the MCP server itself is still required.
3. Only after all checks pass ‚Üí proceed with GodotPrompter plan ‚Üí GDAI MCP execute ‚Üí GDAI MCP verify.

### Notify the user when unavailable

Always report clearly if any of these are missing:

- `godot-mcp`, `godotiq`, `godot-mcp-pro`, or `gamelab-mcp` not in Cursor MCP server list
- `GAMELAB_API_KEY` not set in Cursor Secrets
- Blender not installed (`bash tools/install_extended_toolchain.sh`) ‚Äî required for M5 turntable QA
- GDAI HTTP `:3571` not responding (`curl http://127.0.0.1:3571/tools`)
- Godot Editor not running
- GDAI plugin folder missing (`game/addons/gdai-mcp-plugin-godot/`)

**Do not silently fall back to manual file edits.**

