## 1. Roles & responsibilities (R&R) ‚Äî GodotPrompter + MCP stack

Core tools are **complementary, not alternatives**. P0 MCP (`godot-mcp`, `godotiq`, `godot-mcp-pro`) is **required**; art generators are tiered per `docs/art/ART_AUTOMATION_PIPELINE.md`.

### Tool A: GodotPrompter ‚Äî *Architect & code generator*
| | |
|---|---|
| **Role** | Structural planner, GDScript author, custom spatial shader architect |
| **Owns** | Shader code (`.gdshader`), GDScript logic (`.gd`), math, class design, signal wiring patterns, refactor plans, procedural generator scripts |
| **Responsibility** | Godot 4 syntax; NPR/toon pipelines; stepped diffuse ramps; vertex shaders (water, wind sway); typed GDScript |
| **When to use** | **First** ‚Äî before GDAI touches scenes: plan approach, draft shaders/scripts, define node structure |
| **Does NOT** | Replace the editor for placing meshes, tuning light angles, or reading live editor errors |

### Tool B: GDAI MCP ‚Äî *Scene mutator & runtime verifier*
| | |
|---|---|
| **Role** | Editor integration layer ‚Äî creates/configures nodes, scenes, materials, lights, `WorldEnvironment` |
| **Owns** | `.tscn` graph changes, inspector properties, in-editor playtest, output-panel error inspection |
| **Responsibility** | Apply zone palettes from art docs; parent nodes; assign materials; audit FPS in editor |
| **When to use** | **After** GodotPrompter planning ‚Äî implement the plan in the open Godot Editor |
| **Prerequisite** | `bash tools/ensure_gdai_mcp.sh` passes; `godot-mcp` connected in Cursor MCP |

### Tool C: Godotiq ‚Äî *Analyze & debug*
| | |
|---|---|
| **Role** | Signal tracing, dependency graphs, debug console, `ui_map`, `verify_project_runs` |
| **Owns** | Read-only diagnosis ‚Äî why combat hung, orphan signals, runtime errors |
| **When to use** | After a failure or before refactoring systems with many signals |
| **Does NOT** | Edit `.tscn` or mutate scenes |

### Tool D: Godot MCP Pro ‚Äî *Automated testing*
| | |
|---|---|
| **Role** | L4/L5 scenarios ‚Äî `run_test_scenario`, `assert_screen_text`, input replay, screenshot compare |
| **Owns** | Test assertions and scripted playthroughs (`--minimal` mode ‚Äî no scene editing) |
| **When to use** | Phase gates, combat/menu E2E, regression after narrative changes |
| **Does NOT** | Build or edit scenes (GDAI only) |

### Tool E: GameLab Studio MCP ‚Äî *UI art generate* (required)
| | |
|---|---|
| **Role** | Ink-wash UI frames, combat icon sheets, VFX sprite sheets via MCP |
| **Owns** | Exported PNG/WebP under `game/assets/textures/ui/` |
| **When to use** | UI borders, menu frames, icon sheets ‚Äî **not** default zone tileables |
| **Does NOT** | Place nodes, assign materials, or edit `.tscn` ‚Äî hand off to GDAI MCP |
| **Prerequisite** | `gamelab-mcp` + API key; `palette_remap.py` after every gen |

### Tool F: ComfyUI / Material Maker ‚Äî *Zone NPR albedos* (offline)
| | |
|---|---|
| **Role** | Stylized tileable wood, stone, ground; hero texture sheets |
| **When to use** | Zone albedos per `docs/art/ART_AUTOMATION_PIPELINE.md` ¬ß3 |
| **Handoff** | `palette_remap.py` ‚Üí register ‚Üí GDAI material assign |

### Tool G: AI 3D + Blender ‚Äî *Hero pipeline + turntable QA* (required offline)
| | |
|---|---|
| **Role** | Automated stylized meshes (Meshy/Tripo/Rodin) + GLB export |
| **When to use** | Characters, torii, lacquer box, palace trim per `CHARACTER_BIBLE.md` |
| **Handoff** | Mixamo rig ‚Üí Godot import ‚Üí GDAI MCP placement |

### Tool H: ACE-Step 1.5 ‚Äî *Audio prototype*
| | |
|---|---|
| **Role** | Zone BGM, opening movie, boss loops, boss intro cinematics, ending hero scores |
| **When to use** | Every audio pass; pair with `generate_game_audio.py` for instant fallback |
| **Install** | `bash tools/install_ace_step.sh` ‚Üí Gradio or REST API |
| **Generate** | `bash tools/generate_ai_bgm.sh --category opening\|boss_cinematic\|ending\|zone` |
| **Ship rule** | Curated ACE-Step exports + loudness normalize ‚Äî `docs/audio/AUDIO_PRODUCTION_GUIDE.md` |

### Rejected for v1 (do not adopt)
- **Summer Engine** ‚Äî replaces Godot editor; breaks GDAI stack
- **Fennara** ‚Äî fourth scene editor; overlaps GDAI/Godotiq/MCP Pro
- **Ink narrative rewrite** ‚Äî JSON spine already defined
- **Notion MCP** ‚Äî `docs/` + `game/data/` are authoritative; no duplicate index
- **Kenney town kits** ‚Äî wrong visual read for Japanese coastal JRPG

### Combined workflow (default ‚Äî use every session)

```
0. BOOT     ‚Üí bash tools/ensure_gdai_mcp.sh (block if GDAI MCP unavailable ‚Äî notify user)
1. READ     ‚Üí docs/art/RENDERING_GUIDE.md + zone row in ENVIRONMENT_KITS.md
2. PLAN     ‚Üí GodotPrompter: shader design, script structure, node tree, property values
3. EXECUTE  ‚Üí GDAI MCP: create/edit scenes, apply materials, configure lights & WorldEnvironment
4. VERIFY   ‚Üí GDAI MCP: run scene (F5), read editor errors/output, check visuals in viewport
5. REFINE   ‚Üí GodotPrompter: fix script/shader bugs GDAI surfaced ‚Üí GDAI MCP applies fixes in editor
6. ASSETS   ‚Üí Procedural audio/art via project tools; GDAI MCP assigns in editor
7. QA       ‚Üí L0‚ÄìL2 every commit; art/flow QA per task (see ¬ß0 QA stack below)
8. SHIP     ‚Üí commit; acceptance gates + bash tools/check_asset_compliance.sh
```

**Handoff rules:**
- GodotPrompter **writes** code; GDAI MCP **applies** it to the project and **confirms** it runs.
- **Never** stop after GodotPrompter output alone ‚Äî always hand off to GDAI MCP for editor integration.
- **Never** hand-edit `.tscn` or inspector values in Cursor when GDAI MCP is available.
- Never configure complex shaders purely by hand in the inspector without GodotPrompter drafting the `.gdshader` first.
- If GDAI reports script errors ‚Üí loop back to GodotPrompter for the fix, then GDAI MCP to re-test.

**Sprint factory telemetry (event-driven PM):**
- Workers: `run_agent_session_gate.sh` opens session ‚Üí `pm_emit_cycle_event.sh agent_cycle_complete` closes it + auto-fetches tokens (`CURSOR_API_KEY`).
- Policy: `docs/qa/AGENT_SESSION_TELEMETRY.md` ¬ß9 ‚Äî wired into orchestrator, watchdog, stakeholder reports.

**Cross-cutting factory features (agents MUST register before merge):**
- Registry: `game/data/qa/workflow_integration_registry.json` ‚Äî every PM hook, secret, telemetry, or watchdog feature.
- Before merge: `bash tools/check_feature_integration.sh --remind` ‚Üí `L0_workflow_integration` PASS.
- Authority: `docs/qa/WORKFLOW_INTEGRATION.md`.

