## 2. Stylized rendering rules (project-specific)

When configuring nodes, environments, or materials, enforce **Tides of Urashima** standards ‚Äî not generic bright anime defaults.

### A. Lighting & shadows
- **Shadows ON:** Use `DirectionalLight3D` with `shadow_enabled = true` and soft shadow filter. Tune max distance per zone.
- **Colored lights ‚Äî never pure white:** One dominant directional + one colored fill per zone (`docs/art/RENDERING_GUIDE.md` ¬ß5).
  - Village: cool overcast `#B8C8D8` + warm lantern `#D4A880`
  - Caves: cyan emissive `#4AE8D8` fill; no sky
  - Palace: gold `#FFD890` from above; void sky `#1A1A3A`
- **Muted, not pastel-bright:** Fog grey `#8B9DAF`, weathered wood `#5C4A3A`, biolume `#4AE8D8`. Avoid candy colors and sunny anime gold skies in the hub.
- **No heavy SSIL/SSAO:** Disable in v1 ‚Äî muddies toon ramps (`docs/art/RENDERING_GUIDE.md` ¬ß3.2).

### B. WorldEnvironment & post-processing
- **Tonemap:** `TONE_MAPPER_FILMIC` or `TONE_MAPPER_ACES` ‚Äî **not** Linear (washed out). Tune exposure so fog and emissives do not clip to white.
- **Fog:** Distance fog **always on** in ruined village hub. Zone-specific density; fog color matches sky palette.
- **Volumetric fog:** Subtle in village only ‚Äî not caves or palace void.
- **Glow (bloom):** Enable on emissive content ‚Äî lacquer box, cave algae, palace gold trim, spirit VFX. Mode `Softlight`; intensity restrained (~0.3‚Äì0.4). **Not** blanket dreamy bloom on every scene.
- **Skip:** SDFGI, VoxelGI (v1), HDR reflections, lens flare.

### C. Sky
- Use **ProceduralSkyMaterial** per zone ‚Äî grey overcast coast, dark caves, void palace. **No** sunny PhysicalSky HDRI or photographic skies.

### D. NPR materials & textures
- **Toon ramp shader family** across the scene ‚Äî single cohesive look (`ART_DIRECTION.md` ¬ß7).
- **Automated stylized albedo** on all hero assets (ComfyUI/Material Maker + `palette_remap.py`); light normal maps OK for wood/stone detail.
- **No full PBR workflow:** Avoid metallic/glossy skin, ORM packs, StandardMaterial3D realism in player-facing scenes.
- **Emission:** Lacquer box (3 glow states), algae, palace trim, spirit lower body (alpha/additive).
- **Outlines:** **Optional / subtle only** ‚Äî not required. Prefer readable silhouettes and value contrast over heavy inverted-hull outlines unless art review approves.
- **Water:** Stylized planes + foam decals + custom shader ‚Äî not fluid simulation.

### E. Environment & foliage
- Wind-sway vertex shaders OK for coastal grass/reeds.
- Japanese coastal / ry≈´g≈´ motifs only ‚Äî **no** European castle kits, medieval props, or Kenney placeholders in ship builds.
- **No primitive placeholders** (`BoxMesh`, `CapsuleMesh`) in player-facing scenes ‚Äî build via GDAI MCP + NPR meshes/shaders or licensed art.

### F. Audio
- **Procedural placeholders:** `python3 tools/generate_game_audio.py --all` (ORIGINAL, copyright-safe).
- **Ship target:** Curated authored tracks per `docs/audio/AUDIO_PRODUCTION_GUIDE.md` ‚Äî all registered in manifest.
- **Never** import random web SFX/BGM without documented license.

